---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BookmarkModals from '../components/BookmarkModals.astro';
---

<Layout title="My Folders">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <header class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center justify-between gap-4 mb-8">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-text-main tracking-tight mb-2">My Folders</h1>
        <p class="text-surface-400">Organize your saved AI conversations into folders.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <button id="btn-create-folder-main" class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-500 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-xl font-medium transition-all shadow-lg shadow-primary-500/20 active:scale-95">
          <i data-lucide="folder-plus" class="w-5 h-5"></i>
          <span>Create Folder</span>
        </button>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="flex-1 overflow-y-auto min-h-0 pr-2 pb-10">
      <div id="folders-container" class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <!-- Folders will be rendered here -->
      </div>
      
      <div class="hidden flex-col items-center justify-center h-64 text-surface-500" id="empty-state">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-surface-800 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4 border border-surface-700">
          <i data-lucide="folder-plus" class="w-8 h-8 text-surface-400"></i>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xl font-medium text-text-main mb-2">No folders yet</p>
        <p class="text-sm mb-6 text-center max-w-sm">Create your first folder to start organizing your AI conversations and bookmarks.</p>
        <button id="btn-create-folder-empty" class="bg-surface-800 hover:bg-surface-700 text-text-main px-6 py-2.5 rounded-xl font-medium transition-colors border border-surface-700 flex items-center gap-2 active:scale-95">
          <i data-lucide="plus" class="w-4 h-4"></i> Create Folder
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SEO Content Section (Visually Hidden but readable by Google) -->
  <section class="sr-only">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-main">RBookmark: The Ultimate Custom Bookmarker App</h2>
    <p>
      In today’s fast-paced digital landscape, information overload is a genuine challenge. Whether you are conducting deep research, saving long-form AI conversations, or just trying to organize your favorite digital resources, having a reliable <strong>bookmarker</strong> is no longer just a luxury—it is an absolute necessity. Welcome to RBookmark, the premier <strong>bookmarker app</strong> designed from the ground up to help you categorize, manage, and retrieve your most valuable data with unprecedented ease.
    </p>
    
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mt-8">Why Do You Need a Dedicated Bookmarker?</h3>
    <p>
      The internet is vast, and built-in browser features often fall short when it comes to true organization. A standard <strong>bookmark</strong> saves a URL, but it doesn't preserve the context, the exact text snippet, or the nuances of a complex AI chat. This is where a <strong>custom bookmark</strong> solution becomes critical. With RBookmark, you are not just saving a link; you are capturing ideas in their entirety. As a highly versatile <strong>website bookmarker</strong>, our platform allows you to create dedicated folders, add searchable tags, and even store rich text directly in your dashboard. 
    </p>
    
    <p>
      Many users find themselves asking: should I use a traditional browser <strong>bookmark or bookmarker</strong> tool? The answer lies in the complexity of your workflow. If you only need to return to a simple homepage, a standard browser bookmark might suffice. However, if you are a developer, a student, a writer, or a researcher dealing with complex AI-generated outputs, specific code snippets, or lengthy articles, you need a powerful <strong>bookmarker</strong> capable of handling structured data securely. RBookmark fills this exact gap, serving as your personal, highly organized knowledge base.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mt-8">Features That Make RBookmark the Best Bookmarker App</h3>
    <p>
      What exactly sets RBookmark apart from any other generic <strong>website bookmarker</strong>? First and foremost, it is our <strong>custom bookmark</strong> organizational system. Instead of throwing all your saved items into a chaotic, endless list that is impossible to navigate, you can structure your knowledge into beautifully designed, distinct folders. 
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 mt-4">
      <li><strong>Rich Text Editing & Preservation:</strong> Save exactly what matters. Use our Notion-style expanded view to read, edit, and organize your saved content. Your <strong>custom bookmark</strong> retains its formatting, making it perfect for code blocks or structured essays.</li>
      <li><strong>Cloud Sync & Local Fallback:</strong> Whether you want your <strong>bookmarker app</strong> connected to the cloud via Supabase for cross-device synchronization, or you prefer a strictly local, privacy-first approach using your browser's storage, RBookmark adapts to your specific security needs.</li>
      <li><strong>Lightning Fast Search:</strong> Our <strong>bookmarker</strong> comes equipped with instant, real-time search capabilities. You can locate any specific <strong>custom bookmark</strong> by querying its title, its content body, or its associated tags instantly.</li>
      <li><strong>Advanced Export Capabilities:</strong> Unlike a standard browser <strong>bookmark</strong>, our robust tool allows you to export your saved text directly to beautiful PDF documents or plain TXT files. This gives you total ownership and portability of your data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mt-8">The Future of the Website Bookmarker</h3>
    <p>
      The frustrating days of disorganized folders, dead links, and lost context are finally over. When considering whether to rely on a native OS <strong>bookmark or bookmarker</strong> utility designed for the modern web, remember that a dedicated <strong>bookmarker app</strong> provides features specifically tailored for deep, uninterrupted work. RBookmark ensures that every single <strong>custom bookmark</strong> you create is safely stored, easily retrievable, and beautifully formatted. 
    </p>
    <p>
      We understand that an effective <strong>website bookmarker</strong> must be fast, responsive, and reliable across all devices. That is why our application is built using cutting-edge web technologies, ensuring a seamless experience whether you are on a desktop workstation or a mobile device.
    </p>
    <p>
      Start using RBookmark today to completely transform how you save and interact with the web. Our ongoing mission is to provide the most intuitive, visually appealing, and robust <strong>website bookmarker</strong> experience available anywhere. Save your best ideas, safely categorize your AI chats, organize your research, and never lose a crucial piece of information again. Experience the profound difference a true, dedicated <strong>bookmarker</strong> makes in your daily productivity.
    </p>
  </section>

  <BookmarkModals />

</Layout>

<script>
  import { getFolders, type Folder } from '../lib/dataClient';
  
  async function updateView() {
    const container = document.getElementById('folders-container');
    const emptyState = document.getElementById('empty-state');
    if (!container || !emptyState) return;

    // Show loading skeleton
    container.innerHTML = `
      <div class="glass-panel p-6 animate-pulse flex items-center justify-between shadow-md">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <div class="p-3 w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-surface-700 border border-surface-600"></div>
          <div class="w-32 h-6 rounded bg-surface-700"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-surface-700"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-panel p-6 animate-pulse flex items-center justify-between shadow-md">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <div class="p-3 w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-surface-700 border border-surface-600"></div>
          <div class="w-32 h-6 rounded bg-surface-700"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-surface-700"></div>
      </div>
    `;
    emptyState.classList.add('hidden');
    emptyState.classList.remove('flex');
    container.classList.remove('hidden');

    let folders = await getFolders();
    folders = folders.filter((f: Folder) => f.name.toLowerCase() !== 'clipboard');

    if (folders.length === 0) {
      container.classList.add('hidden');
      emptyState.classList.remove('hidden');
      emptyState.classList.add('flex');
    } else {
      emptyState.classList.add('hidden');
      emptyState.classList.remove('flex');
      container.classList.remove('hidden');
      
      container.innerHTML = folders.map((f: Folder) => `
        <a href="/folder?id=${encodeURIComponent(f.id)}" class="glass-panel p-6 group hover:border-primary-500/50 transition-all duration-300 flex items-center justify-between shadow-md hover:shadow-lg">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="p-3 rounded-xl bg-primary-500/10 text-primary-400 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300 border border-primary-500/20">
              <i data-lucide="folder" class="w-6 h-6"></i>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-text-main group-hover:text-primary-400 transition-colors capitalize">${f.name}</h3>
            </div>
          </div>
          <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-5 h-5 text-surface-500 group-hover:text-primary-400 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-all"></i>
        </a>
      `).join('');
      
      // Re-initialize icons for newly rendered content
      // @ts-ignore
      if (window.lucide) window.lucide.createIcons();
    }
  }

  function attachListeners() {
    const btnMain = document.getElementById('btn-create-folder-main');
    const btnEmpty = document.getElementById('btn-create-folder-empty');
    
    const openFolderModal = () => window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('openFolderModal'));
    
    // Remove existing listeners to avoid duplicates if attachListeners is called multiple times
    if (btnMain) {
      btnMain.removeEventListener('click', openFolderModal);
      btnMain.addEventListener('click', openFolderModal);
    }
    
    if (btnEmpty) {
      btnEmpty.removeEventListener('click', openFolderModal);
      btnEmpty.addEventListener('click', openFolderModal);
    }
  }

  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    updateView();
    attachListeners();
  });
  
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', () => {
    updateView();
    attachListeners();
  });
  
  window.addEventListener('foldersUpdated', updateView);
  window.addEventListener('auth-changed', updateView);
</script>
